t in fayetteville nc the announcement came in response to local media reports in may claiming traces of genx had been found in the local cape fear river and north carolina drinking water trace genx amounts in the cape fear river to date have been well below the health screening level announced by the north carolina department of health and human services on  june said the dupont performance chemicals spinoff in a june  statement the company it added continues to believe that emissions from its fayetteville facility have not impacted the safety of drinking water but the wilmington del company said it would capture remove and safely dispose of wastewater that contains the byproduct genx as part of its role as a big employer in the community the capture and removal of this wastewater starts june  the move follows a  decision by the then dupont unit to phase out perfluorooctanoic acid pfoa at the fayetteville site due to its toxic nature genx is used to replace pfoa which is an ingredient in its teflon brand chemours said it would continue to work closely with local and state officials to answer questions provide information as needed and determine next steps chemours is also being investigated by the netherlands for alleged dumping of the substance into water the company has responded to allegations by the dutch minister of infrastructure and environment that the contamination in the nearby merwede river had occurred through the air chemours which has used genx instead of pfoa at this european site since  has been permitted to emit the compound gemx into the atmosphere in the netherlands the companys main production site for fluoropolymers in europe is based in dordrecht the netherlands newsletter signup sign up for the pn daily report more pn newsletters ›› most popular berry worker dies in industrial accident news wednesday july  foxconn picks wisconsin for us plant news wednesday july  plastics news now plastics industry comes to washington to talk to lawmakers multimedia thursday july  retirement in the pipeline for ads ceo sort of news tuesday july  saintgobain eyes  million expansion in michigan news wednesday july  read next news some growth but commodity resin sales not very strong overall news plastics executives seek trump bump for their agenda news clariant part of ethylene purchasing market investigation subscribe view all newsletters register this weeks issue latest news impacting the global plastics industry past issues july   july   june   subscribe sign up breaking news and indepth coverage of essential topics delivered straight to your inbox view all newsletters connect with us register to access our archive of leading information on the plastics industry follow plasticsnews copyright   crain communications inc  privacy  terms chemours  wikipedia chemours from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the chemours company type public traded as nyse cc sp  component industry performance chemicals titanium dioxide viton founded   headquarters wilmington delaware united states area served global key people mark p vergnano ceo richard h brown chairman products products list teflon titanium dioxide viton opteon freon revenue us billion  operating income us million  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us million  subsidiaries subsidiaries list antec international website chemourscom the chemours company commonly referred to as chemours is an american chemical company that was founded in july  as a spinoff from dupont it has its corporate headquarters in wilmington delaware united states contents  history  products  corporate governance  board of directors  senior executives  references  external links historyedit in october  dupont announced that it was planning to spin off its performance chemicals business into a new publicly traded company in mid dupont filed its initial form  with the sec in december  and announced that the new company would be called the chemours company the spinoff to dupont shareholders was completed on july   and chemours stock began trading on the new york stock exchange on the same date its  shares of common stock were distributed to dupont shareholders at a par value of one cent each chemours has assumed various liabilities arising from lawsuits against dupont encountered in the normal course of business productsedit chemours manufactures and sells performance chemicals falling within three segments titanium technologies titanium dioxide fluoroproducts refrigerants and industrial fluoropolymer resins and derivatives including freon teflon and viton and chemical solutions cyanide sulfuric acid aniline methylamines and reactive metals corporate governanceedit board of directorsedit mark p vergnano curtis v anastasio bradley j bell richard h brown chairman of the board mary b cranston curtis j crawford dawn l farrell stephen d newlin senior executivesedit mark p vergnano chief executive officer mark e newman senior vice president and chief financial officer e bryan snell president  titanium technologies paul kirsch president  fluoroproducts christian w siemer president  chemical solutions david c shelton general counsel and corporate secretary beth albright senior vice president human resources erich parker corporate communications and chief brand officer referencesedit  a b c d e cc income statement  balance sheet  cash flow  chemours company the common s stock  yahoo finance retrieved january     casey simon october   dupont to spin off performance chemicals unit to shareholders  bloomberg bloomberg news retrieved december     stynes tess december   dupont names planned performance chemicals spinoff the wall street journal retrieved december     dupont completes spinoff of the chemours company prnewswire press release wilmington del july   retrieved july     information statement the chemours company report the chemours company june   pp cover   f–   a b c d e f g chemours  leaders in the chemical industry the ch