ening as they unfold back next next tweet from user chemours  wikipedia chemours from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the chemours company type public traded as nyse cc sp  component industry performance chemicals titanium dioxide viton founded   headquarters wilmington delaware united states area served global key people mark p vergnano ceo richard h brown chairman products products list teflon titanium dioxide viton opteon freon revenue us billion  operating income us million  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us million  subsidiaries subsidiaries list antec international website chemourscom the chemours company commonly referred to as chemours is an american chemical company that was founded in july  as a spinoff from dupont it has its corporate headquarters in wilmington delaware united states contents  history  products  corporate governance  board of directors  senior executives  references  external links historyedit in october  dupont announced that it was planning to spin off its performance chemicals business into a new publicly traded company in mid dupont filed its initial form  with the sec in december  and announced that the new company would be called the chemours company the spinoff to dupont shareholders was completed on july   and chemours stock began trading on the new york stock exchange on the same date its  shares of common stock were distributed to dupont shareholders at a par value of one cent each chemours has assumed various liabilities arising from lawsuits against dupont encountered in the normal course of business productsedit chemours manufactures and sells performance chemicals falling within three segments titanium technologies titanium dioxide fluoroproducts refrigerants and industrial fluoropolymer resins and derivatives including freon teflon and viton and chemical solutions cyanide sulfuric acid aniline methylamines and reactive metals corporate governanceedit board of directorsedit mark p vergnano curtis v anastasio bradley j bell richard h brown chairman of the board mary b cranston curtis j crawford dawn l farrell stephen d newlin senior executivesedit mark p vergnano chief executive officer mark e newman senior vice president and chief financial officer e bryan snell president  titanium technologies paul kirsch president  fluoroproducts christian w siemer president  chemical solutions david c shelton general counsel and corporate secretary beth albright senior vice president human resources erich parker corporate communications and chief brand officer referencesedit  a b c d e cc income statement  balance sheet  cash flow  chemours company the common s stock  yahoo finance retrieved january     casey simon october   dupont to spin off performance chemicals unit to shareholders  bloomberg bloomberg news retrieved december     stynes tess december   dupont names planned performance chemicals spinoff the wall street journal retrieved december     dupont completes spinoff of the chemours company prnewswire press release wilmington del july   retrieved july     information statement the chemours company report the chemours company june   pp cover   f–   a b c d e f g chemours  leaders in the chemical industry the chemours company  retrieved may    external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to chemours official website v t e chemours corporate directors richard h brown curtis j crawford mark p vergnano products teflon titanium dioxide viton subsidiaries and joint ventures antec international divisions and facilities dupont building notable people éleuthère irénée du pont alfred i du pont eugene du pont francis gurney du pont francis irénée du pont henry du pont lammot du pont pierre s du pont anthony joseph arduengo iii roy j plunkett frederick n tebbe chadwick a tolman history dupont du pont family hagley museum and library eleutherian mills v t e philadelphiaarea corporations including the delaware valley list of companies base